 > I have what may be a real "novice" question. When PGP is finally
 >"cracked/broken" will it then be a relatively simple matter to decode
 >data encrypted with it ? Or will it be neccessary to mount the same massive
 >initial effort for each attempt at decrypting a message ? I hope someone
 >can help me with this as i am a real newcomer to this forum.

  If there is some fundamental breakthrough in cracking RSA, then PGP keys
will be easily breakable.  Otherwise, "breaking" PGP would have to be done
by slogging through each message individually.

